------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------"Castlevania: Symphony of the Night - Arcane Engine ReImagined (AERI) Config File"-------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                    "Hello and thanks for checking out to SOTN AERI"
                           "You can use this config file to cusomize various elements of AERI"


------------------------------------------------------------
-- "COMPATIBLE CONTROLLER BIND NAMES LIST"
------------------------------------------------------------
"Script uses BizHawk's internal controller config rebinds, use names in this list when setting custom binds IN THIS CONFIG FILE"
"Script grabs your emulator binds from the contol mapper menu; Config > Controllers... > Normal Controls > Virtual Port 1 - DualShock"
"If setting a custom bind IN THIS CONFIG FILE to keyboard use the specific key name in CAPS if applicable"
"*ALL REBINDS MUST BE EITHER KEYBOARD KEYS OR COMPATIBLE CONTROLLER BINDS OR IT MAY THROW ERRORS*"

"------DO NOT EDIT------"

"D-Pad Up"
"D-Pad Down"
"D-Pad Left"
"D-Pad Right"

"△"
"X"
"□"
"○"

"L1"
"L2"
"R1"
"R2"

"------DO NOT EDIT------"

------------------------------------------------------------
-- "SPELL CASTING OPTIONS"
------------------------------------------------------------
"Set specific selection keys for each spell and a global cast button"
"Compatible with BizHawk's controller config rebindings, see compatible binds list at start of config"

"Press button to cast selected spell"
Cast_Selected_Spell: "L2"

"Press button to clear spell memory"
Clear_Selected_Spell: "End"

"Press button to store selected spell in memory"
Summon_Spirit_Select: "Keypad1"
Tetra_Spirit_Select: "Keypad2"
Hellfire_Select: "Keypad3"
Dark_Metamorphosis_Select: "Keypad4"
Soul_Steal_Select: "Keypad5"
Sword_Brothers_Select: "Keypad6"


------------------------------------------------------------
-- "MOVEMENT ASSIST OPTIONS"
------------------------------------------------------------
"Optional toggles for easier movement and QoL"
"Compatible with BizHawk's emulator controller config rebinding, see compatible binds list at start of config"

"Double tap Left or Right in bat to wing smash, keep holding directional input to chain"
Enable_Wing_Smash_Assist: "true"

"Press button to wolf dash, hold directional input to continue sprinting"
Enable_Wolf_Dash_Assist: "true"
Wolf_Dash_Button: "○"

"Double tap Up to gravity jump, continue holding to chain until next landing (will automatically uses double if applicable)"
Enable_Gravity_Jump_Assist: "true"

"Hold to auto-chain shield dashes (requires a shield in offhand [○] slot)"
Enable_Shield_Dash_Assist: "true"
Shield_Dash_Button: "△"


------------------------------------------------------------
-- "TIMING TUNER"
------------------------------------------------------------
"Use these options to tune frame timings for your specific core to speed execution or fix dropped inputs"
"Default values tested for SOTN NymaFastCore (https://github.com/MottZilla/SOTN_NymaFastCore)"
"GCD and buffer values clamp to GCD = (5 + (spellsteps * spellstepframes)) and BUFFER = (GCD + 5 frames)"

"GLOBAL VALUES"
"STEPFRAMES: Frames/input step of execution, reduce this for faster execution at the risk of dropped inputs"
"GLOBALCOOLDOWN: Duration until the program can call another spell, runs at spell call | Does not override native input lockouts after spells"
"BUFFER: Duration that the program will still recognize an input after release, runs during cooldown"

"SHIELD DASH VALUES"
"INTERVALWAIT: Delay between Triangle[△] (dash) and Circle[○] (shield cancel) inputs"
"AUTOFIREDELAY: Delay before next back dash can start"


"Wing Smash Defaults: {STEPFRAMES: 2, GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 60, BUFFER: 15}"
Wing_Smash_STEPFRAMES: "2"
Wing_Smash_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "60"
Wing_Smash_BUFFER: "15"

"Wolf Dash Defaults: {STEPFRAMES: 3, GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 40}"
Wolf_Dash_STEPFRAMES: "3"
Wolf_Dash_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "40"

"Gravity Jump Defaults: {STEPFRAMES: 2, GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 60}"
Gravity_Jump_STEPFRAMES: "2"
Gravity_Jump_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "60"

"Shield Dash Defaults: {INTERVALWAIT: 7 AUTOFIREDELAY: 3}"
Shield_Dash_INTERVALWAIT: "7"
Shield_Dash_AUTOFIREDELAY: "3"


"Summon Spirit Defaults: {STEPFRAMES: 2, GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 65}"
Summon_Spirit_STEPFRAMES: "2"
Summon_Spirit_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "65"

"Tetra Spirit Defaults: {GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 110}"
Tetra_Spirit_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "110"

"Hellfire Defaults: {STEPFRAMES: 2, GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 135}"
Hellfire_STEPFRAMES: "2"
Hellfire_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "135"

"Dark Metamorphosis Defaults: {STEPFRAMES: 2, GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 110}"
Dark_Metamorphosis_STEPFRAMES: "2"
Dark_Metamorphosis_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "110"

"Soul Steal Defaults: {STEPFRAMES: 2, GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 120}"
Soul_Steal_STEPFRAMES: "2"
Soul_Steal_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "120"

"Sword Brothers Defaults: {GLOBALCOOLDOWN: 140}"
Sword_Brothers_GLOBALCOOLDOWN: "140"


------------------------------------------------------------
-- "CUSTOM UI OPTIONS"
------------------------------------------------------------
"Enable or disable various HUD elements, no I will not let you turn off the AERI logo :)"

"Toggles the dagger on the MP bar showing projected MP after casting"
Enable_MP_Bar_Dagger_UI: "true"

"Toggles spell name display and cooldown bar"
Enable_Spellbook_UI: "true"

"Toggles MP cost displayed to the left of the cooldown bar"
Enable_Spell_Cost_UI: "true"

"Displays which assist functions are enabled"
Enable_Active_Assists_UI: "true"

"Toggles library card count display"
Enable_Library_Card_Count_UI: "true"

